ows and methodologies Work with engineers and managers to schedule projects, assign resources and provide schedule updates and roadmaps Define, evolve and implement the strategy for continual improvement of design tools and flows as internal and external tools, flows and technology requirements evolve Manage training delivery to the engineering design teams Coordinate activities of domain experts to deliver coherent methodology Establish and maintain technical and commercial relationships with external suppliers and maximize benefit to the organization Manage EDA budget and license forecasting Staff management, including recruitment, appraisal, motivation and team building Lead a team of Methodology/EDA/CAD/Design Engineers Required Skills and Qualifications Minimum of a Bachelor of Science degree in Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering, Computer Science or closely related field with 10 years of experience in IC Design or CAD Engineering, with a minimum of 5 years in a managerial position. Demonstrated experience with multiple CAD flows: backend, frontend, validation, and digital verification methodologies Proven communicator with a track record of delivering technical solutions and satisfying customers Deep understanding of project execution requirements Ability to Identify and analyze problems, device plans and implement solutions Excellent communication skills with an ability to reduce complex info into easy to digest form for upper management and/or key customers Ability to lead multi-stream projects within a fast moving and changing business environment Thorough knowledge of industry tools and techniques Deep understanding of digital, analog, mixed signal IC design flows Data Management tool experience, perforce (preferred), svn, design sync An innovative, creative, lateral thinking problem solver Consistent track record of uncompromising customer orientation to deliver leading-edge solutions Strong team development and management skills to enable the creation of a highly capable and sustainable organization Comfortable handling multiple concurrent tasks This position is located in Austin, TX Cirrus Logic is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. We strive to select the best qualified applicant for any opening and to reward employees based on their skills, experience and performance. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, national origin, pregnancy status, marital status, gender, age, religion, physical or mental disability, medical condition, veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity, genetic information or any other characteristic protected by law. ", 
